FBIS3-48602 "dreas018_i_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-018 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Jan 1994 Cambodia Two Vietnamese `Agents' Captured in Battambang BK2701040194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 26 Jan 94 BK2701040194 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia Language: Cambodian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] According to a report from Moung Russei District, Battambang Province, the inhabitants of Tuol Roka village in the Russei Krang commune have captured two Vietnamese communist agents. The agents were planted in the village to carry out the Communist Party of Vietnam's policies in Cambodia and lead the networks of the puppet Cambodian People's Party [CPP] and puppet administration in the districts, communes, and villages. The report says that the people captured these two Vietnamese communists after discovering their identity. They found out that these two have often met with and made reports to the Vietnamese in Moung District. They are both Vietnamese nationals who speak Cambodian. They are in charge of the CPP and the Vietnamese communist puppets and their administration in Moung District and the Ta P'de-Kaos Kralar area. [passage omitted]
